      <hedline>
        <hl1>Casualties of War</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Milton Leitenberg letter on May 14 review of Michael Ondaatje's novel Anil's Ghost holds virtually all specialists estimate 60,000 people have died in Sri Lankan civil war</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Michael Ondaatje's novel ''Anil's Ghost,'' reviewed on May 14, concerns the civil war in Sri Lanka. This war has been going on since the early 1980's. Your reviewer wrote, ''The estimated 20-year toll is 17,000 dead.'' Virtually all specialists on the conflict use estimates in the range of 60,000 killed.</p>
        <p>Milton Leitenberg  College Park, Md.</p>
      </block>
